1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,500
Start on the exact operational screen for this guide.

2
00:00:02,500 --> 00:00:05,000
Bookings is the triage queue, not the place to guess or skip record review.

3
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:07,500
Search only when you know the booking code, customer, phone, email, or vehicle.

4
00:00:07,500 --> 00:00:10,000
Lifecycle chips narrow the queue by the actual operating problem.

5
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:12,500
Verify the row: booking code, customer, vehicle, dates, status, and total.

6
00:00:12,500 --> 00:00:15,000
Approve only when the request can be fulfilled; otherwise open the record or decline with a reason.

7
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:17,500
Do not approve if payment, insurance, pickup, or vehicle availability is unclear.

8
00:00:17,500 --> 00:00:20,000
Review customer, vehicle, dates, and status before opening a record.
